<subSubSection id="D305DBC801B7F255592EB6D155EF24FF" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" type="description">
<paragraph id="44B44EF255661DD774367B1422BCCFEA" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F02A0DFFF30A261A0289CB222A149CCA" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">
A small cushion plant, 7-13 cm in diameter with a stout woody taproot, stem sericeous. Leaves sessile, 2-3 
<normalizedToken id="F38CAFDF14A158FC5DC78C67308D1B4B" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.2-0.4 cm, linear to linear-oblanceolate, acute, entire, base attenuate, grey sericeous-pubescent on the lower surface and margins of upper surface, glabrous on central area. Flowers solitary or paired, sessile or on very short terminal peduncles up to 10 mm long; bracteoles linear, 3 
<normalizedToken id="D9C4788E5DB6BD130A5F66809B14FAEF" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.5 mm, pedicels 2 mm; outer sepals 5-6 
<normalizedToken id="503BE00450181C4320B48A079B327544" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2 mm, lanceolate, obtuse, pilose; inner sepals ovate, c. 4 mm wide, membranous, abruptly narrowed to a green, pilose mucro; corolla 1.6-1.7 cm long, white, lobed with red, pubescent, midpetaline bands terminating in a broadly triangular lobe; ovary conical, pilose at apex; style pilose, divided c. 4 mm above base, stigmas 3 mm. Capsule and seeds not seen. [
<bibRefCitation id="FC164E1FE2E3A0017360E92D1EC3E2DD" author="Sa'ad, F" journalOrPublisher="Bronder Offset, Rotterdam" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" pagination="1 - 287" refId="B314" refString="Sa'ad, F, 1967. The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht. Bronder Offset, Rotterdam: 1 - 287" title="The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht" year="1967">
<normalizedToken id="208B5AA79C1C134A960EEB1A9CB0964B" originalValue="Sa’ad">Sa'ad</normalizedToken>
1967
</bibRefCitation>
: 146]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FBE6695ECFD199A81BC712759F5B557D" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="810445908144EFE18419A1B7D6938B8E" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0988F29670CFCF33F69793B537DB9C0C" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">
Morocco (
<emphasis id="1B93A4426AF926C89F4B4CC07DB5619C" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Jury et al.</emphasis>
17622, 
<emphasis id="50D4AB6CD8FC84DB85EBB16761BC7C69" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Balls</emphasis>
3086, 
<emphasis id="51CD38FD877C6D7E6A71FFBEE07B16C3" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">
<normalizedToken id="8D6B42DECC7F4030EB5F4FE41CDF184B" originalValue="Güemes">Gueemes</normalizedToken>
et al.
</emphasis>
1577). 2000-3000 m on limestone rocks, somewhat disjunct in distribution in the High Atlas, Middle Atlas and the Rif mountain ranges.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="44E984FA7C78BDD7158859E03D79C62D" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" type="notes">
<paragraph id="017A6AD8B4F6172FFE279D9D66139FEE" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6B27ABA971269E673DD5F874C410BD47" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">
Dwarf plants of 
<taxonomicName id="FB1A01DD39EA77A6ACEE4C9A0E0DA3CC" authorityName="L., Syst. Nat. ed. 10, 2: 923. 1759. (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1759" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus lineatus" order="Solanales" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lineatus">
<emphasis id="B669CDE50C0E95B1AD80A24E0B08F8D3" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Convolvulus lineatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar but have longer sepals and corollas and the upper surface of the leaves are uniformly sericeous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
